proxiableUUID().details: Implementation of the ERC-1822 {proxiableUUID} function. This returns the storage slot used by the implementation. It is used to validate the implementation's compatibility when performing an upgrade. IMPORTANT: A proxy pointing at a proxiable contract should not be considered proxiable itself, because this risks bricking a proxy that upgrades to it, by delegating to itself until out of gas. Thus it is critical that this function revert if invoked through a proxy. This is guaranteed by the `notDelegated` modifier.

addSupportedToken(address).notice: Marks a token as supported. Once supported, tokens cannot be un-supported.

availableBalance(address,address).notice: The balance that is available to the depositor, subject to deposits having been observed by the operator in a finalized block and no attestations having been issued but not yet burned by the operator

balanceOf(address,uint256).notice: The balance of a depositor for a particular token and balance type, compatible with ERC-1155

balanceOfBatch(address[],uint256[]).notice: The batch version of `balanceOf`, compatible with ERC-1155

denylist(address).notice: Denylists an address from interacting with the contract

depositFor(address,address,uint256).notice: Deposit tokens on behalf of another address after approving this contract for the token

Deposit tokens with an ERC-3009 authorization

initialize(address,address,address[],uin.notice: Initializes the contract and all of its modules, in the order of inheritance

initiateWithdrawal(address,address,uint2.notice: Starts the withdrawal process on behalf of a depositor who has authorized the caller. After `withdrawalDelay` blocks, `withdraw` may be called to complete the withdrawal. Once a withdrawal has been initiated, that amount can no longer be used. Repeated calls will add to the amount and reset the timer.

initiateWithdrawal(address,uint256).notice: Starts the withdrawal process. After `withdrawalDelay` blocks, `withdraw` may be called to complete the withdrawal. Once a withdrawal has been initiated, that amount can no longer be used. Repeated calls will add to the amount and reset the timer.

isAuthorizedForBalance(address,address,a.notice: Check if an address is currently authorized to withdraw and transfer tokens on behalf of a depositor

isBurnSigner(address).notice: Whether or not an address is a valid burn signer that may sign the calldata for burning tokens that have been minted using the `GatewayMinter` contract

isDenylisted(address).notice: Whether or not a given address is denied from interacting with the contract

isTokenSupported(address).notice: Whether or not a token is supported

isTransferSpecHashUsed(bytes32).notice: Whether or not a transfer spec hash has been used

pauser().notice: The address with the `pauser` role that can pause and unpause the contract

removeBurnSigner(address).notice: Removes an address from the set of valid burn signers

removeDelegate(address,address).notice: Stop allowing `delegate` to withdraw or transfer the caller's `token` balance. This revocation is not respected for burn intents that have already been signed, so that burns cannot be prevented by removing the delegate.

totalBalance(address,address).notice: The total balance of a depositor for a token. This will always be equal to the sum of `availableBalance` and `withdrawingBalance`.

unDenylist(address).notice: Allows a previously-denylisted address to interact with the contract again

updateDenylister(address).notice: Sets the address that is allowed to modify the denylist

updateFeeRecipient(address).notice: Sets the address that will receive the fee for burns

updatePauser(address).notice: Sets the address that may call `pause` and `unpause`

updateWithdrawalDelay(uint256).notice: Sets the number of blocks that must pass before a withdrawal can be completed. Care must be taken for the difference between `block.number` and RPC block number for certain networks.

withdraw(address,address,address).notice: Completes a withdrawal that was initiated at least `withdrawalDelay` blocks ago, on behalf of another depositor. The funds are sent to the specified recipient.
